
==Description==

"Watchdog networks drive public debate, boost transparency and ignite movements for change. In a world where major problems are increasingly understood as global, and where governments are slow to respond, watchdog networks are on the leading edge of using new technology to take action with credible data. Across every major global issue, from human rights to the environment, watchdog networks are leveraging the power of technology, online communication and social media to sort through layers of information, to create a better society."
(http://gsnetworks.org/blog/new-reportwatchdog-networks/)

